abstract: Census Bureau reports that median residential rent in New York City has risen 3.4 percent over past three years while median household income has risen only 1.1 percent; says about 30 percent of city's renters pay at least half of income on housing.
lead_paragraph: A report from the Census Bureau shows that lower-income tenants continue to be caught in a housing squeeze that shows no signs of abating.

headline.main: New York Rents Outpaced Inflation Over 3 Years, Census Data Say
headline.print_headline: City Rents Outpaced Inflation Over Past 3 Years, Census Report Says
